00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,550
Alright, real talk,  predict what happens next.

2
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:09,868
If you get it right, you're already thinking like a senior engineer.

3
00:00:09,868 --> 00:00:24,921
Records written inside an open transaction are written to the partition log immediately , but are invisible to consumers with isolation.level=readcommitted until the transaction commits.

4
00:00:24,921 --> 00:00:29,250
Aborted transaction records are also skipped.

5
00:00:29,250 --> 00:00:39,500
The consumer's effective read position is bounded by the Last Stable Offset (LSO) — the offset up to which all transactions are resolved.

